-- Sanctions Violate Human Rights to Peace, Rohani Tells UN
-- B y   K a m b i z   F o r o o h a r
-- 2013-09-24T21:22:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-24/sanctions-violate-human-rights-to-peace-rohani-tells-un.html
Iranian President Hassan Rohani
told the United Nations today that his country poses no threat
and that economic sanctions violate human rights to peace and
development.  Sanctions cause “belligerence, war-mongering and human
suffering,” and common people are victimized, Rohani said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kambiz Foroohar in  New York  at 
 kforoohar@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
